Would absolutely recommend eating here. Awesome character, delightful food, good service. 5 stars.
I hate most people and food too.

Lock the doors and shut off the lights! After hours dinner here is something special ;-)

Order some takeouts, they overcharged me $70. I did not realize it until a few days later. I then called them, some dude told me to call them next day. And of course I called my bank immediately, I’m glad the bank gave the money back. I don’t understand why they did this, i only order 2 items and I tipped them already, like how come you charged me triple the price. Is the checkout guy blind or something? The food is also overpriced. The fried rice I order was trash, it tasted like it was leftovers from a few days ago. VERY BAD.

This place is a giant scam. They ask you for deposit and don’t show prices of anything. We made a reservation for 20 people and let them know only 15 were coming. They still charged us $40/person for 20 total. Our original bill was around $400 and when my husband gave his credit card, they charged us closer to $1000.
We came here for the pork bao but they were sold out and we got the dumplings instead; Still very good and customer service was great. We are coming back to try their famous Lan's Old Town!
A review will not do it justice. Don't come here for the food. Best karaoke i've done in awhile

Come here if you want to have fun but be treated terribly and have them take your money.  I had my birthday party here and made a reservation for 18 people. I paid the $200 deposit that is “required” the week before the reservation. I was never told anything g more than don’t bring a birthday cake or decoration but “bring lots of alcohol”. Being as not everyone can always make a party and people cancel last minute, only 14 people ended showing up. When I got the bill it was significantly more expensive than I had predicted. The music was blasting and the server was pushing for me to pay and so I got everyone’s cash and couldn’t figure out why the bill was still so high.  I ended up paying the difference and obviously had had some drinks in me so it was hard to understand. The next morning I realized that they had charged me for 18 people (what my reservation was originally for). So I was overcharged by 4 people. I called the “restaurant” immediately when they opened and a female worker answered and asked if I knew about the reservation policy and of course no one had told me this. She said it wouldn’t be a problem then and would call back about the refund.  Of course no one called me back. The next day I called and a man answered he proceeded to yell at me and tell me it was my fault that I didn’t let him know 4 people didn’t show up. My question was why couldn’t the server count the amount of people at my table? No response. I proceeded to get yelled at by three men on the phone and they harassed me and told me it’s not their problem, they’re not refunding me, and that I should ask my friends for the money I paid. I was appalled. They didn’t even give me a receipt for the final bill, and I was unable to dispute the charge for it because of it. Don’t go here if you want to be ripped off. This place is barely legal. No one checked IDs when we walked through the doors, the food is barely edible, the owner was passing out and stumbling from drinking too much alcohol.  If I could give negative stars I would. Once again, it was fun but would rather not be ripped off again.
Only go here if you want to party hard. Feel free to stand on the bar and take a pull from a bottle of booze. Food was not good but that's not what you go for.
Great fun.

Wow what a interesting place to be honest the food should get 5 stars but I ordered the house fried rice and I got shrimp fried rice witch was fresh , tasty and they’ll give you everything you need to eat at home ....
Great food
So overpriced. The owner was incredibly rude and aggressive towards my female friends. Seriously no one should go here. If anyone else has experienced unwanted sexual behavior please report
This place is nuts
Some of the best Chinese food in Chicago!
Yummy
I found the whole experience horribly overpriced for the quality of food and service.
The food is AWFUL & salty. The owner is extremely rude & aggressive towards women.
Rudest owner and dirty restaurant. Would never go back.
Great atmosphere! Bring friends and put your party pants on.

Has life become mundane? Are the Chicago winters too long and does your boss suck? Shake it off and spice it up. Go get lit at Lan’s Old Town. This place is Disney for adults, minus the screaming brats and cry babies. Treat yourself to following and you’ll have memories for a lifetime: 9 pm dinner fri or sat It’s family style so get your reservation for 8-10 of your friends/people you’d love to see get smash happy and sing karaoke on the bar top of a Chinese restaurant. The owner, Jimmy locks the door at 9 so get there before and don’t be late. Make about 150-220 Jell-O shots of assorted colors and liquors. You know the drill, Vodka with green and yellow, Rum with red and blue. Bring as much liquor as you’d like and plenty of beers (1-2 coolers worth). The sooner you pass around the shots the sooner the madness begins. Crank up the Miley Cyrus, try a little “Call Me Maybe” by Carly Rae Jepsen and smash hits from the 2000’s. Get loose, dance on the bars, take your shirts off and get wild. This is YOUR night. You deserve it. Just about everything goes. Except for breaking plates. Don’t break the plates. This isn’t a Greek wedding. If you’re a few people short for a reservation feel free to drop me a line. If I’m in town isn’t love to be a part of your special night.
Best Chinese food I’ve had in as long as I can remember! So good, great service and fast!
5/5. Jimmy is a Chicago icon.  9 PM friday and saturday night are the best times to go and start your night.  Bring plenty of drinks.
This place is fing awesome. Words cannot explain. You just have to go and experience it.
Lan's is lit!!! Looking for great food, byob, amazing atmosphere where you can dance on the chairs and bar too? You get it all here!! Perfect place for birthday parties, you will not be disappointed.
This is hands down the most wild thing I’ve encountered.  BUCKLE UP
not a restaurant, more of a public drinking place and no one has to clean up. gets wild. one of a kind
Fun party spot!
Wild good time. Would like more food. Very small dishes
Such good byob

Made a reservation for a table with friends. As soon as we took our last bites, we were kicked off of the table. Ridiculous, considering we were charged a BYOB fee and weren't finished with our drinks.
Great BYOB. Great Food. Very charismatic and friendly owner.

Party restaurant.  Took forever for the food to come out and it was extremely mediocre.  The owner's behavior really isn't appropriate either, especially around women, even if some people like how he gets into the party.
See for yourself. I've been here three things in one year and I kinda wish it was more often.
This is my third time hear for my birthday wirh my family always have a blast on Saturday night with karakoe and the food is delicious
Amazing. You must go here with your friends as a group. Foods so so but trust me your not there for the food!
The best restaurant , friday and saturday so fun
I mean
Love this place like I love tacos

If you're picking up, beware!! Their pricing here on Google is $2-3 dollars less per dish than actuals, and they're unapologetic about it when you ask them. They know it's wrong and they haven't updated it, despite having time and money to print out new brochures with their updated pricing.  The food is 4 or 5 stars, just know you're going to get hit with a higher bill once you actually arrive to pick up your food.
Looks like a good place to have a small group events. Lan (I believe) is a cool dude and very accommodating. Had a nice edm Playlist going; could be loud if you get triggered or like safe spaces.
It's clean it's quiet it's simple it's cute. Food is really good!
Pretty good food and the owner is a character

Probably the most interesting restaurant I have ever been to. Food was excellent and its byob, but the atmosphere created by the owner Jimmy really makes the place.  It's an experience you wont forget. Expect dance music to be blasting and frequent friendly conversations with the owner it between his dancing. We had a ton of fun and can't wait to go back.
Good
An experience that goes beyond the great food
Worst place I've been in a long time. Complete rip off. $40 per person in exchange for 2 hours of waiting and 2 bites of food. Avoid this place at all costs
Amazing food, as long as you don't get the fried rice.  Lan's spicy pork is amazing!

Delicious Chinese food! Kung Pao dish, which has won numerous awards, was fantastic. I ordered it with tofu instead of chicken and it was the BEST tofu. Perfectly crispy triangle type tofu. Everyone else ordered meat dishes and raved about them. Fantastic noodle dishes as well. 4 stars since its a different environment, very "homey". TV is usually on instead of music and staff isn't too professional. Very friendly though! Just a very causal local setting.
Great experience. Must come with a group on a Friday/Saturday night.
Great food, friendly, neighborhood atmosphere.  We eat here at least once a week and would recommend it to everyone.

I was excited to try a new place in Old Town, boy did I make a terrible choice. Myself and 4 of my friends went on Friday evening at 7pm. We walked in and it was completely empty. The "hostest" asked us how many and we told her 5 and then she asked if we made a reservation. Reservation for what, there is NO ONE HERE! So we waited 10 mins while she hemmed and hawed about seating us. Once we were seated she told us that we had to leave at 9pm and that there was a $5 cork fee for BYOB (which we thought was $5 a table but it was $5/person). Also we had to order $15 of food/ person. The food was Okay (other than the shrimp entree one person ordered, she said it was really good). So, save the time and money and go somewhere else.

I've been searching for a good Chinese place in the city for years. I'm a sucker for a good Mu Shu dish and Lan's knocked it out of the park! They also have an option for lettuce wraps, which I love when I am trying to be healthy! The delivery guys are always so nice and the chef likes to write me little notes on my lettuce wrap container. What's not to love about that?  An extra bonus, I heard this place has killer Karaoke at night. I'll have to check it out!

Worst place ever I've been to. Total ripoff. Don't waste your money here. Food is just OK and over priced. You have to spend $15 per person on Fri and Sat nights. It's BYOB but they charge you $5 per person. Service is horrible as well.
Found this place randomly and was thrilled with our experience.  We loved the service, atmosphere and food.  We definitely will be returning.

Just ordered this place for delivery.  Was told it would take 20-60 mins for delivery but an hour and 15 mins later after my food did not arrive I had to call.  She said it wasn't in the kitchen so it must be on the way.  25 mins after this I called again and she said she couldn't get a hold of her driver but took my number down and said she would call me back...She didn't and I had to call back just to be put on hold again.  The lady at Lans came back 5 mins later and said sorry the order was never given to the kitchen and there is nothing she can do.  Unfortunately, this poor service and unwillingness to correct their mistake will make me never order from this place again.

Love, love, love this place. Fresh, tasty and some of the best Chinese food I've had in this city. The owner is very attentive and took the time to recommend several dishes to my vegetarian friend. Major plus, it's BYOB!
I got the fried rice and loved it! I noticed someone else wasn't too pleased with it... maybe my standards for fried rice are lower than his ;)  Service was okay. Will be back.
Sort of a hidden gem in Old Town. Solid beef & broccoli great mooshu chicken & a lot of different vegetarian options. BYO option helps you save a bit as well.
Lans sweet and sour chicken hit the spot. I ordered delivery, and everything I had was great. Really enjoyed the  kung pao chicken, Szechwan beef and I always love crab rangoon.
This has been our go-to place for Christmas Eve/Day Chinese food for the past few years. They have all of the staple dishes and the egg drop soup and spicy Szechuan beef.

soooo good. the mu shu pancakes are handmade and delicious. check out the scallops with cucumber. a great place to start your friday or saturday night with it being byob. If you stay late enough, karaoke from behind the bar.
